WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:25.987 --> 00:00:26.373
So, let me start over.

00:00:43.360 --> 00:00:48.070
As Diana and I were driving around, we sang the first song a lot like what we're playing.

00:00:48.070 --> 00:00:58.720
But I want to go over this and tell you all, as I have been trying really hard to convey to you what the Spirit of the Lord was telling us about prayer.

00:00:59.880 --> 00:01:14.240
Whenever I went through the portal and the Lord allowed me to talk to Sister Lucy, she said, "The greater glory will not come by tongues alone, but by travail.

00:01:14.240 --> 00:01:14.577
" Travail.

00:01:14.577 --> 00:01:23.240
And so whenever I was talking about travail, I don't want to flippantly talk about it and act like, "Oh yeah, you just do this," and it's flesh.

00:01:23.240 --> 00:01:30.070
It's only by the Spirit of the Lord that you get into the river to that point of travail.

00:01:30.070 --> 00:01:34.320
And that takes a lot of maturity in praying.

00:01:34.320 --> 00:01:38.790
It is something that you cultivate with the Holy Spirit.

00:01:38.790 --> 00:01:43.760
And you get there by praying His heart.

00:01:43.760 --> 00:01:52.175
If you are praying the Father's heart for souls, you will get into that travail that I'm talking about.

00:01:52.175 --> 00:01:55.080
But you don't do that in the flesh.

00:01:55.080 --> 00:01:57.600
It is by the Spirit of the Lord.

00:01:58.080 --> 00:01:59.520
You need to know this.

00:01:59.520 --> 00:02:06.520
I was corrected, and I don't want to lead people wrong.

00:02:07.140 --> 00:02:10.600
You'll get people who get flaky, thinking they can get there by themselves.

00:02:11.440 --> 00:02:19.983
You just walk around going to church, trying so hard, making weird noises, and thinking that you're in travail in the natural, in your flesh.

00:02:23.760 --> 00:02:33.526
But when it is truly Holy Spirit-inspired, you are yielded to and controlled by the Holy Spirit.

00:02:33.891 --> 00:02:39.000
You are only getting there through the Holy Spirit, through intercession.

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:49.751
So, you're not going to automatically sit on your couch and be like, "I'm just going to tap into these groanings and make noises," because you can get real flaky with it.

00:02:49.751 --> 00:02:54.280
I was instructed—I talked to my friend Gina.

00:02:54.280 --> 00:03:01.600
I've always told you she's my prayer mentor who I learned from when I worked at the big ministry.

00:03:02.151 --> 00:03:10.070
She said there were groups a couple of decades ago that had groaning meetings.

00:03:11.220 --> 00:03:19.640
They would go and just groan in the spirit, but be in the flesh and act weird.

00:03:19.915 --> 00:03:21.840
You can get real flaky with this.

00:03:24.053 --> 00:03:32.910
The intimacy it takes is praying and travailing over souls for the heart of the Father.

00:03:32.910 --> 00:03:34.320
What's on the Father's heart?

00:03:34.320 --> 00:03:36.663
This is a different intimacy level.

00:03:36.994 --> 00:03:42.537
It's a maturity level of your intercessory prayer with the Father.

00:03:43.166 --> 00:03:47.657
When you're travailing in the Spirit, you're getting it by the Spirit.

00:03:47.657 --> 00:03:49.480
It's not flesh.

00:03:49.480 --> 00:03:54.140
So, I don't ever want to make it into something where people ask, "Well, Brandon, how do I get there?

00:03:54.140 --> 00:03:57.400
" You get there by praying in the Spirit, praying in the Spirit, and praying in the Spirit.

00:03:59.234 --> 00:04:01.533
Then you start yielding to the Spirit, and yielding to the Spirit.

00:04:05.760 --> 00:04:08.415
Sometimes travail comes out as crying tears.

00:04:08.415 --> 00:04:20.359
Like Gina was telling me today on the phone, she said, "Brandon, whenever I get in travail, it's like you're weeping before the Father for souls.

00:04:20.359 --> 00:04:27.880
" Praying for the lost, you're weeping for the lost, and you're praying the heart of the Father.

00:04:27.880 --> 00:04:29.100
His heart is souls.

00:04:29.100 --> 00:04:32.943
That's what He said: "My heart is the harvest, every time.

00:04:32.943 --> 00:04:52.975
" That's why I came across really strong when I said that if you are truly prophetic, if you are truly called to the ministry, and you sit there and tell me, "Brandon, I know the Father, I know I'm called to the ministry," and you never give an altar call...

00:04:54.000 --> 00:05:00.780
I would have to say—and that's why I come across so strong—that you're a false prophet and you are not hearing the voice of God.

00:05:00.780 --> 00:05:05.360
Am I saying you are listening to the devil by calling you a false prophet?

00:05:05.360 --> 00:05:05.620
No, I'm not.

00:05:05.620 --> 00:05:07.246
I'm not being mean.

00:05:07.246 --> 00:05:12.733
I'm saying it's false by you not having a heart for the harvest.

00:05:12.733 --> 00:05:15.560
His heart is for the harvest.

00:05:27.420 --> 00:05:37.269
It's always going to bring in that which was lost, to leave the 99 to go after the one, to pray over North Korea, to weep for the ones that are bound by the demonic, to travail for them, and to pull them out of darkness.

00:05:41.920 --> 00:05:42.327
And it's not just by tongues.

00:05:42.327 --> 00:05:49.200
It's by entering into the river of the heart of the Father for that intercessory prayer time.

00:05:49.200 --> 00:05:52.160
Does what I'm saying tonight make sense?

00:05:57.467 --> 00:05:57.716
I don't ever want to make this flaky.

00:05:57.964 --> 00:06:02.360
I take great responsibility in leading so many of you in prayer.

00:06:05.200 --> 00:06:10.560
Like I said, I thank God for the elders to correct me, because Brandon Biggs doesn't have it all.

00:06:13.765 --> 00:06:19.480
And I'm going to tell you, even with the little bit that I know, I feel like I have a lot of room to grow.

00:06:19.480 --> 00:06:23.427
I'm so thankful for people like Lynn and Gina.

00:06:23.427 --> 00:06:26.154
People will text and say, "Hey, listen.

00:06:32.326 --> 00:06:32.611
This is a little off; you can correct this.

00:06:32.611 --> 00:06:36.297
" It's just a simple correction, and hey, I'm all for it.

00:06:50.260 --> 00:06:50.550
I just want to tell you all, my heart is to bring in the harvest and to bring in the lost, all for the glory of God.

00:06:50.550 --> 00:06:54.660
It's never about Brandon, never about Diana.

00:06:54.660 --> 00:06:56.960
We are here to serve Jesus.

00:06:56.960 --> 00:07:05.307
We want to be a part of the greatest prayer army this world has ever seen.

00:07:05.307 --> 00:07:19.733
The Lord said, "You will raise up a million-strong prayer army of men and women on this channel, and you will touch the nations for me, and you will bring in this last harvest.

