00:19:49.205 --> 00:19:52.470
'They didn't invite me on the platform.

00:19:55.075 --> 00:19:59.500
I wasn't the one preaching to the crowds or shaking cities with fiery sermons.

00:19:59.500 --> 00:20:06.545
My name was not printed on the flyers, nor did I stand in the spotlight.

00:20:06.545 --> 00:20:10.040
But I assure you, heaven knew my name.

00:20:10.662 --> 00:20:14.880
I was the man groaning on the floor, two floors above the meeting.

00:20:16.220 --> 00:20:20.526
I was the sound you heard in the stillness before the heavens opened.

00:20:20.949 --> 00:20:29.160
I was the one who travailed until the heavens thundered and the demons screamed.

00:20:31.149 --> 00:20:37.840
I was the midwife to revival, and the womb of awakening was soaked with prayer.

00:20:37.840 --> 00:20:41.360
When Charles Finney preached, fire fell.

00:20:48.560 --> 00:20:48.840
But I assure you, the match had already been struck in the prayer chamber.

00:20:48.840 --> 00:20:54.040
My knees broke the ground before his voice did.

00:20:54.040 --> 00:21:02.135
My tears watered the soil of souls before he ever saw their faces.

00:21:05.143 --> 00:21:05.771
I was not his assistant; I was his intercessor.

00:21:09.840 --> 00:21:13.200
And I have come in this hour—yes, this exact moment in history—to speak to those who feel hidden, overlooked, passed by.

00:21:22.314 --> 00:21:22.663
To those who are tired of shallow altars and powerless gatherings.

00:21:22.663 --> 00:21:31.920
To those who have felt the tug of God to weep in secret, fast in silence, and shake the unseen realm.

00:21:34.520 --> 00:21:34.980
You are not weak.

00:21:34.980 --> 00:21:36.664
You are dangerous.

00:21:36.664 --> 00:21:39.533
Revival never starts in the sanctuary.

00:21:39.533 --> 00:21:42.800
It starts in the secret place.

00:21:42.800 --> 00:21:46.250
It erupts from groaning rooms.

00:21:46.250 --> 00:21:53.044
It is born on the bathroom floor at 3 a.

00:21:53.044 --> 00:21:53.462
m.

00:21:53.462 --> 00:21:59.448
It flows from the agony of divine burden and the joy of answered travail.

00:22:01.200 --> 00:22:08.302
And the reason we've seen so many shallow flames in recent years is because the furnace of intercession has gone cold.

00:22:08.302 --> 00:22:12.257
Well, I'm here to fan the flame again.

00:22:12.257 --> 00:22:19.536
In the chapters ahead, I will teach you what it means to prevail in prayer.

00:22:19.536 --> 00:22:26.260
Not just to pray cute prayers, but to wrestle in the spirit until heaven invades earth.

00:22:26.260 --> 00:22:36.800
I will teach you how to pray until demons flee cities, until entire regions come under conviction, until the very air feels charged with glory.

00:23:01.192 --> 00:23:01.808
You don't need a stage to shake nations.

00:23:20.679 --> 00:23:21.329
You need a room, a corner, a mat, a mandate.

00:23:21.329 --> 00:23:36.008
If you're willing to lose your reputation to gain God's attention, if you're willing to bleed in intercession so others can be birthed into the kingdom, then welcome, intercessor.

00:23:36.008 --> 00:23:37.800
You're in the right place.

00:23:37.800 --> 00:23:43.520
Let's go underground so revival can erupt above ground.

00:23:43.520 --> 00:23:45.373
' And that was Father Nash.

00:23:45.373 --> 00:23:59.783
So then we'll go ahead to this part: 'I wasn't the preacher, but I carried the burden, the hidden furnace behind the fire.

00:24:04.480 --> 00:24:04.760
You don't need a pulpit to carry revival.

00:24:07.852 --> 00:24:08.463
You need a burden.

00:24:16.970 --> 00:24:17.255
And I carried one so heavy it bent me to the floor more times than I could count.

00:24:17.255 --> 00:24:25.100
While the world was looking for a stage, I was looking for a corner to kneel in.

00:24:27.715 --> 00:24:35.057
It was there, on hardwood floors and cold upper rooms, that I learned how heaven responds to groaning intercession.

00:24:42.048 --> 00:24:42.332
I didn't envy Finney's crowds.

00:24:43.468 --> 00:24:44.036
I envied the presence.

00:24:48.440 --> 00:24:56.240
And I learned early that if the presence didn't come first, the people would just walk away unchanged.

00:25:13.940 --> 00:25:14.240
What good is a sermon if it hasn't been forged in the furnace of prayer?

00:25:14.240 --> 00:25:16.515
Intercession is not a job.

00:25:16.515 --> 00:25:22.297
It's a calling to bleed in secret so others can be healed in public.

00:25:22.297 --> 00:25:26.424
If Finney was the sword, I was the whetstone.

00:25:29.080 --> 00:25:33.790
And my place was not beside him on the platform, but before him in the prayer room.

00:25:33.790 --> 00:25:37.063
Groaning in secret, shaking in public.

00:25:37.063 --> 00:25:43.143
I remember once arriving in a city days before the revival meetings began.

00:25:43.143 --> 00:25:46.420
I didn't go out to greet the leaders.

00:25:46.420 --> 00:25:49.840
I didn't set up the chairs or hand out flyers.

00:26:05.200 --> 00:26:05.467
I found a small inn with a secluded room and went straight to travail.

00:26:16.994 --> 00:26:17.366
I groaned until my body shook, and until the innkeeper knocked, concerned someone was dying in that room.

00:26:17.366 --> 00:26:19.600
He wasn't wrong.

00:26:19.600 --> 00:26:22.130
I was dying.

00:26:22.130 --> 00:26:26.165
Dying to flesh, dying to apathy, dying to my will.

00:26:32.160 --> 00:26:32.480
And in that death, something glorious was born.

00:26:37.569 --> 00:26:37.733
An atmosphere so thick with God's presence that conviction would later fall without a single word preached.

00:26:37.733 --> 00:26:41.000
People say they want revival, but do they want this?

00:26:46.760 --> 00:26:48.748
The unseen weeping, the burdened praying, the spiritual midwifery that leaves you depleted and unnoticed.

00:26:48.748 --> 00:26:52.240
Revival doesn't come through talent.

00:26:52.240 --> 00:26:55.740
It comes through tears.

00:26:57.500 --> 00:26:59.429
I was never invited to the revival for applause.

00:27:01.856 --> 00:27:02.008
In fact, I rarely stayed for the services.

00:27:02.008 --> 00:27:11.600
I had one assignment: birth the move of God and get out of the way.

00:27:31.600 --> 00:27:31.880
And if I could be honest with you, beloved, I loved it that way.

00:27:31.880 --> 00:27:39.022
There is a sacred joy in anonymity when you're walking in divine assignment.

00:27:45.320 --> 00:27:46.300
You don't need to be known on earth when you're shaking hell in heaven's war room.

00:27:52.840 --> 00:27:53.255
The demons know your name, and that's enough.

00:27:53.255 --> 00:27:58.640
Your greatest effectiveness will never be seen by men.

00:27:58.640 --> 00:28:00.789
It will be known in eternity.

00:28:00.789 --> 00:28:07.460
When you pray, fast, groan, and birth breakthroughs behind the curtain, heaven moves and the kingdom advances.

00:28:07.460 --> 00:28:14.674
Never trade the glory of hidden obedience for the fading applause of the spotlight.

00:28:14.674 --> 00:28:18.635
' I'm going to keep reading.

00:28:18.635 --> 00:28:20.680
'I didn't start on my knees.

00:28:20.680 --> 00:28:24.503
